    "description": "<h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Learning, but with a Light Touch !</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >If math feels as indigestible as a litter box to you, this game might just change that! Dive into a playful and colorful world where trigonometry becomes a true <strong><u>narrative game</u></strong>, filled with humor and lovable characters.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3288520/extras/6ce3f509efa91bd7d7feff3c4b3e9807.poster.avif?t=1762009975\" width=640 height=360 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3288520/extras/6ce3f509efa91bd7d7feff3c4b3e9807.webm?t=1762009975\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3288520/extras/6ce3f509efa91bd7d7feff3c4b3e9807.mp4?t=1762009975\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Light Touch , but withlearning!</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >In <strong>La Litière Trigo</strong>, trigonometry will no longer be an abstract concept !</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >The game focuses on explaining not only <u><strong>the essential basics</strong></u> but also <strong>the &quot;why&quot; behind the math</strong>. Through light dialogue and accessible explanations, the concepts become concrete and easy to understand.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >A training tailored to your level will be offered to you during the final phase !</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >This game is literally a <strong>private tutoring session</strong> in the form of a video game.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3288520/extras/9f331952aa899a7ab4a5cc92cc058eb1.avif?t=1762009975\" width=668 height=1002 /></span></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >For what levels?</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>La Litière Trigo</strong> is designed for students who are just beginning to learn about trigonometry, like <strong>sine</strong> and <strong>cosine</strong>, and continues through to more advanced concepts like <strong>the unit circle</strong> and <strong>radians</strong>:</p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>United States </strong>: generally introduced in <strong>10th or 11th grade</strong> as part of Algebra 2 or Precalculus​</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>United Kingdom </strong>: Basic trigonometry concepts are usually introduced in <strong>Year 10</strong> and continue into <strong>Year 11</strong> with more advanced applications covered in <strong>A-Level Maths</strong> for older students.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Australia </strong>: concepts often appear during <strong>Year 9</strong>, with more advanced concepts covered in <strong>Year 10</strong> or <strong>11</strong> as part of Precalculus or higher math courses.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Canada - Quebec </strong>: is introduced in <strong>4e secondaire</strong>, with more advanced topics continuing into <strong>5e secondaire</strong></p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Canada - outside Quebec</strong> : generally introduced as part of <strong>Algebra 2</strong> or <strong>Precalculus</strong>, often in <strong>10th or 11th grade</strong>.</p></li></ul><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3288520/extras/0e1879b6c341142998915f2f04d52e15.poster.avif?t=1762009975\" width=640 height=360 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3288520/extras/0e1879b6c341142998915f2f04d52e15.webm?t=1762009975\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3288520/extras/0e1879b6c341142998915f2f04d52e15.mp4?t=1762009975\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >This game is suitable for students aged 13 to 17, depending on the country, but it’s also useful for anyone looking <strong><u>to strengthen or review their trigonometry basics</u></strong>.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p>",
